issue.body:
To make the AI assistant more context-aware, allow it to use these Language Server Protocol (LSP) features:
 * Diagnostics: Let the LLM see errors/warnings to self-correct its suggestions.
 * Go-to-Definition: Allow the LLM to look up the source code of functions and variables.
 * Find-References: Allow the LLM to see where code is being used.


To upvote this issue, give it a thumbs up. See [this list](https://github.com/editor-code-assistant/eca/issues?q=is%3Aissue+is%3Aopen+sort%3Areactions-%2B1-desc) for the most upvoted issues.

issue.title: Can't enchant Nexo Items in anvil.
issue.body: ### Describe the bug Bedrock Players cannot upgrade nexo items with enchanted books, it just cancels the action and prevents the upgrade. By nexo Items, I mean an item I give to players using the [Nexo](https://mcmodels.net/products/13172/nexo) plugin. VIDEO: https://gyazo.com/0a9ef3cc0cc8b5081d3f53883b55c136 ### To Reproduce 1. Have a NEXO item, unenchanted or not enchanted at all. 2. Have a enchanted book, that applies to the item you're working with. 3. Try to add/combine the enchanted book to the enchants on the sword, if no enchants, then you're trying to add it with the book. 4. Notice you cannot complete the action, it just cancels it. ### Expected behaviour For the enchants to apply, like it does in vanilla....? ### Screenshots / Videos https://gyazo.com/0a9ef3cc0cc8b5081d3f53883b55c136 ### Server Version and Plugins ### Geyser Dump https://dump.geysermc.org/9Ywpr3VEh7oPaDFv3LOiDLePkFqHu61x ### Geyser Version 2.8.3-SNAPSHOT ### Minecraft: Bedrock Edition Device/Version Windows 11? issue.title: Any tools that return a LINK message (via create_link_message) no longer work.
issue.body: ### Self Checks - [x] I have read the [Contributing Guide](https://github.com/langgenius/dify/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md) and [Language Policy](https://github.com/langgenius/dify/issues/1542). - [x] This is only for bug report, if you would like to ask a question, please head to [Discussions](https://github.com/langgenius/dify/discussions/categories/general). - [x] I have searched for existing issues [search for existing issues](https://github.com/langgenius/dify/issues), including closed ones. - [x] I confirm that I am using English to submit this report, otherwise it will be closed. - [x] & Non English User - [x] Please do not modify this template :) and fill in all the required fields. ### Dify version 1.7.2 ### Cloud or Self Hosted Self Hosted (Docker), Cloud ### Steps to reproduce 1. Install any official plugins which contains any tools with `create_link_message`. 2. Create workflow or chatflow and place the tools. 3. Try to invoke the tool which will return LINK type message. To easy to reproduce the issue, I've attached minimal tool here: [link_demo.zip](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/21822961/link_demo.zip) (rename zip to difypkg to install) This is the minimal tool to reproduce: ```python from collections.abc import Generator from typing import Any from dify_plugin import Tool from dify_plugin.entities.tool import ToolInvokeMessage class LinkDemoTool(Tool): def _invoke(self, tool_parameters: dict[str, Any]) -> Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]: yield self.create_link_message("https://dify.ai/") ``` Affected official plugins are: ```bash $ grep -rE '^\s+yield self\.create_link_message' ./tools ./tools/hackernews/tools/get_story_info.py: yield self.create_link_message(story_url) ./tools/telegraph/tools/telegraph.py: yield self.create_link_message(ph_link) ./tools/spotify/tools/spotify_get_track.py: yield self.create_link_message(track_info["preview_url"]) ./tools/searchapi/tools/google.py: yield self.create_link_message(link=result) ./tools/searchapi/tools/google_jobs.py: yield self.create_link_message(link=result) ./tools/google_calendar/tools/create_event.py: yield self.create_link_message(created_event["htmlLink"]) ./tools/zoom/tools/zoom_update_meeting.py: yield self.create_link_message(updated_meeting["join_url"]) ./tools/zoom/tools/zoom_list_meetings.py: yield self.create_link_message(meeting["join_url"]) ./tools/zoom/tools/zoom_get_meeting.py: yield self.create_link_message(meeting_info["join_url"]) ./tools/zoom/tools/zoom_create_meeting.py: yield self.create_link_message(meeting_info["join_url"]) ./tools/wolframalpha/tools/wolframalpha.py: yield self.create_link_message(response_data["queryresult"]["sources"]["url"]) ./tools/twitter/tools/get_user_info.py: yield self.create_link_message(profile_url) ./tools/twitter/tools/send_tweet.py: yield self.create_link_message(f"https://twitter.com/user/status/{tweet_id}") ``` ### Expected Behavior The link message has been returned. ### Actual Behavior ```bash Run failed: (psycopg2.errors.InvalidTextRepresentation) invalid input syntax for type uuid: "" LINE 3: WHERE tool_files.id = ''::UUID ^ [SQL: SELECT tool_files.id, tool_files.user_id, tool_files.tenant_id, tool_files.conversation_id, tool_files.file_key, tool_files.mimetype, tool_files.original_url, tool_files.name, tool_files.size FROM tool_files WHERE tool_files.id = %(id_1)s::UUID] [parameters: {'id_1': ''}] (Background on this error at: https://sqlalche.me/e/20/9h9h) ```

commits.message:
Security & Documentation Updates

- Fixed persistent database key storage (eliminates backup creation loops)
- Updated terminology from 'military-grade' to 'secured' throughout documentation
- Replaced Microsoft domain examples with generic alternatives
- Added comprehensive SQLite security guide
- Enhanced kill switch documentation with cloud provider disclaimers
- Updated deployment scripts and configuration examples
- Added security-sensitive files to .gitignore

Database Security Improvements:
- Persistent key storage in .sauron_db_key file
- Reduced aggressive key rotation (30 days vs 7 days)
- Smart key loading (env -> file -> generate)
- Proper backup handling for legitimate migrations only
